spanGrp.span: ‘A lady lived in a nice house.
Mãĩ mamita ser-gẽ (hm) estee jũ bá jãrga (_)
Jeska mãĩ michi kabali í wa
Then the cat wanted to… uh…
it wanted to devour a bird.
Then uh… the lady bought a cage and uh… for her bird.
Ñerö este mamita të të jaula tuã'-sã' í í í estee í dú ĩã
The cat wanted to devour the bird;
Ñerö dú biá kete-wã estee michi të
then uh… the bird saw the cat with his binoculars but the cat also saw him.
ñerö (_) estee dú të (_) dú të sũã' estee (hm) binokulo wa í sũã'-ite-ra y michi të sũẽ-gẽ
Then the cat sat down uh…
Ñerö michi michi mẽnẽu-mĩ í jẽk kawã' estee
it swang back and forth on the swing.
jẽk juã' juã' (_) jamĩwa_jiwa jamĩwa_jiwa kolumpio inga
Then the cat came by, saw it; he saw that he was looking at him and so ran away;
Ñerö jeska michi deũ-te të í sũã'/ jie të sũã'-ra jie të sũã-ra jie tunã'
he went to the cage and open its door.
ñerö jie mẽnẽu-te jukö/ í jaula jukö yá-sã'
He left and there the lady saw that the cat was trying to devour him;
í mẽnẽu mãĩ mamita të sũã'-ra estee michi biá-te kete-wã
she hit him so he went away but crashed into the waste basket.
Je kbá-ite mẽnẽu tenã' esteee basurero jãrga
Then the cat came back once more and the lady hit him;
Ñerö (_) (_) michi beteũ-te etabaglö ñerö mamita të í kbá
so he came and walked back and forth.
ñerö estee mãĩ esteee ĩã/ (_) beteũ ñerö shká jamĩwa_jiwa jamĩwa_jiwa
So he went into a pipe;
ñerö mãĩ jẽk pakká-wã tubo jãrga
the little bird ran away quickly and threw something like a stone into the tube uh…
Ñerö estee dú yaba të mãĩ tunã' bue je të este mãĩ jak bi jawãchã' ja/ esteee í e/ í tubo jãrga
And it squashed him and he fell down;
Ñerö je të í aplastá-wã ñerö je jánã
he quickly went into the house.
mãu je je mẽnẽu-mĩ bue jẽk pakká-wã jũ jã/ jũ jãrga
